"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143660","Women and Equalities","false","2019-10-04","<p>The EnAble Fund for Elected Office is a £250,000 interim fund and is available until March 2020 or until the £250,000 budget is exhausted. The Fund supported around 40 candidates at May’s local elections.</p><p> </p><p>We have commissioned an independent evaluation, which will include assessments of average grants made and will be published after the Fund has closed next year.</p><p> </p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2019-10-04T12:31:58.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143660/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143660/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143660/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2019-09-02","EnAble Fund for Elected Office","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, how many candidates have been supported through the EnAble Fund for Elected Office; how much of the £250,000 budget has been allocated; and what the average grant allocated is since the introduction of the scheme.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","285158"
