"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143702","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2019-09-05","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold statistics on the number of requests for diplomatic protection made by British nationals. Any requests for diplomatic protection would be considered on a case-by-case basis, and it is exercised at the Secretary of State's discretion.</p><p>Diplomatic protection is a claim by one State against another in respect of an international legal wrong committed against one of its nationals. Diplomatic protection is extremely rare – the case of Mrs Zaghari-Ratcliffe is the only recent example of where UK has afforded it.</p><p> </p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson",,"2019-09-05T11:24:50.417Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143702/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143702/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143702/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2019-09-02","Diplomatic Service: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many requests for diplomatic protection have been made by British citizens since 2014.","false","Biography information for Hannah Bardell","Livingston","Hannah Bardell","285364"
