"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143839","Department for International Development","false","2019-09-05","<p>Around 100 staff from across the Department for International Development are working to support both DFID’s preparations and preparations across Government for the UK leaving the EU, both with and without a deal.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-09-05T16:22:40.477Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143839/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143839/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143839/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-02","Department for International Development: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many FTE staff in his Department are working on preparations for the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","285408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143840","Department for International Development","false","2019-09-05","<p>DFID operates a flexible working policy and staff hours worked are not tracked centrally by DFID HR in line with DFID policy. As such the information required to answer this question would require collation of individual records held at team level and could only be collated at disproportionate cost.</p>","South West Wiltshire","Dr Andrew Murrison",,"2019-09-05T16:23:37.15Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143840/answer","Biography information for Dr Andrew Murrison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143840/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143840/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-02","Department for International Development: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many hours have staff in his Department spent in each of the last 12 months on preparations in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","285081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143841","Department for International Development","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Government would prefer to leave with a deal and we will work in an energetic and determined way to do so. If it is not possible to reach a deal we will have to leave with no deal and the Government is preparing for that outcome.</p><p>The UK is a development superpower and will remain committed to supporting the world’s poorest and most vulnerable people. Where it is in the UK’s interests, we will seek to work with the EU on shared priorities in international development, as a third country.</p>","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson",,"2019-09-09T16:49:46.26Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143841/answer","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143841/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143841/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-09-02","EU Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what plans his Department has to work with the EU on development co-operation in the event that the UK leaves the EU without a deal.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","285096"
