"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143915","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department is working with its partners across Government, arm’s length bodies, local authorities, industry and the wider health and care system to ensure that all relevant parties are prepared for exiting the European Union. The quality and safety of patient care is paramount in our preparedness plans.</p><p> </p><p>The Department, alongside NHS England and NHS Improvement, is ensuring that there is regular communication with frontline National Health Service organisations and stakeholders in the health and social care sector regarding EU Exit preparations. NHS England will be holding EU Exit Roadshows in the lead up to 31 October, building on the regular communication that the Department and NHS England has with the frontline.</p><p> </p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","285316 ; 286179 ; 286180 ; 286181","2019-09-09T14:58:33.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143915/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143915/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143915/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-02","Department of Health and Social Care: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what meetings his Department has had with Leeds City Council to discuss preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a withdrawal agreement.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","285035"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143916","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-09-09","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams",,"2019-09-09T14:45:31.52Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143916/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143916/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143916/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-09-02","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what meetings her Department has had with Leeds City Council to discuss preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a withdrawal agreement.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","285444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143917","Home Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>It is the duty of any responsible Government to prepare for every eventuality including the scenario that we leave the EU without agreeing a deal.</p><p><br>We are working closely with operational partners - including the police - on contingency planning so we can ensure the safety and security of our citizens in all scenarios.</p><p />","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2019-09-09T14:55:20.543Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143917/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143917/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1143917/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-09-02","Home Office: Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what meetings her Department has had with Leeds City Council to discuss preparations for the UK leaving the EU without a withdrawal agreement.","false","Biography information for Alex Sobel","Leeds North West","Alex Sobel","285118"
