"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142074","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-03","<p>The Department announced in March 2019 that Highways England would work with Transport for the North on a study looking at options for improving road links between the M65 and north and west Yorkshire. The output of this study will inform consideration of the case for future investment.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2019-09-03T16:37:12.067Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142074/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142074/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142074/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-07-25","M65","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has to work with Transport for the North to expand the M65 to Bradford and Leeds.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","282295"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142075","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Government is committed to the conservation and protection of wildlife and we play a leading role internationally in addressing threats to endangered species; for instance through our membership of the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES). Under our obligations as a party to CITES, the Government regulates trade in listed endangered species into the UK under a permitting regime; safeguarding such species from over-exploitation and with the aim of ensuring that international trade in specimens of wild animals and plants does not threaten their survival. Defra coordinates across policy, scientific authorities and enforcement authorities, and engages closely with stakeholders in the UK, to ensure we continue to deliver on our international commitments to protect endangered species under CITES.</p>","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith",,"2019-09-09T11:48:16.22Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142075/answer","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142075/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142075/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-07-25","Nature Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to prevent endangered plant and animal species coming into the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","282289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142076","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-09-09","<p>Defra Ministers have had numerous meetings with their international counterparts in the last year to discuss efforts to protect endangered species from unsustainable and illegal trade and to follow up on commitments made at the international illegal wildlife trade conference held in London last October.</p><p> </p><p>I look forward to continuing discussions on this important issue when I meet with my international counterparts in the future.</p><p> </p>","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith",,"2019-09-09T11:38:48.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142076/answer","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142076/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142076/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-07-25","Nature Conservation: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what meetings she has had with her international counterparts on tackling wildlife crime.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","282290"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142077","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-04","<p>The Department for Transport provides guidance to local authorities and others on the accessibility of the public realm via a comprehensive guidance note entitled “Inclusive Mobility”, which is available on gov.uk . This includes advice on meeting the needs of people who use mobility scooters. The Department is in the process of updating the guidance, and has research underway to inform this. The research is due to conclude by the end of this year, and the updates to the guidance will follow at a later date.</p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2019-09-04T16:35:52.637Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142077/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142077/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142077/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-07-25","Invalid Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to improve pavements and crossings for people who use mobility scooters.","false","Biography information for Andrew Percy","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy","282291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142078","Department for Education","false","2019-09-03","<p>Our ambitions for children and young people with complex special educational needs and disabilities (SEND) are exactly the same as for every other child and young person. As part of this, we are pleased to announce that we will be providing an additional £700 million, 10% in high needs funding next year alone, which will help local authorities to ensure that they can continue to offer the right support for children and young people with the most complex SEND.</p>","Saffron Walden","Mrs Kemi Badenoch",,"2019-09-03T16:43:48.38Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142078/answer","Biography information for Mrs Kemi Badenoch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142078/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1142078/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-07-25","Special Educational Needs: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what plans he has to provide additional funding to local authorities who record an increase in the number of pupils with special educational needs.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","282296"
